import folium
import requests
import math

point1 = (25.789106, -80.226529)
point2 = (18.4663188, -66.1057427)
point3 = (32.294887, -64.781380)
point4 = (25.789106, -80.226529)
list = [point1, point2, point3, point4]
map_osm = folium.Map(location=[25.3, -66.01], zoom_start=5)

folium.PolyLine(list).add_to(map_osm)

x1 = 25.789106
y1 = -80.226529
x2 = 18.4663188
y2 = -66.1057427
x3 = 32.294887
y3 = -64.781380

for number, lat, lon, loc in zip(data["Accident.Number"], data["Latitude"], data["Longitude"], data["Location"]):
   area = abs((x1*(y2-y3) + x2*(y3-y1)+ x3*(y1-y2))/2.0);
   a1 = abs((lat*(y2-y3) + x2*(y3-lon)+ x3*(lon-y2))/2.0);
   a2 = abs((x1*(lon-y3) + lat*(y3-y1)+ x3*(y1-lon))/2.0);
   a3 = abs((x1*(y2-lon) + x2*(lon-y1)+ lat*(y1-y2))/2.0);

   if (area + 0.15 > (a1 + a2 + a3) and area - 0.15 < (a1 + a2 + a3)):
     folium.Marker(
                  location=[lat, lon],
                  popup=loc,
                  icon=folium.Icon(color='blue')
              ).add_to(map_osm)
   else:
      if (not(math.isnan(lat) or math.isnan(lon))): 
        folium.Marker(
                    location=[lat, lon],
                    #popup=loc
                    #icon=folium.Icon(color='red')
                ).add_to(map_osm)

map_osm
